On April 26, 2010, President Barack Obama issued a proclamation to mark the death of Dorothy Height. He ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and all other federal government facilities in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its territories and possessions until sunset on the day of her interment. The flag was also to be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The proclamation was signed on April 26, 2010.